JOHANNESBURG – Former African Union Commission Chairperson Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma has come under fire on Twitter following her tweet about a female president. Dlamini-Zuma said the next president should be a woman who will focus on empowering other women. But many have criticised her, saying she is unfit to be the next leader. Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma is a frontrunner in the race to be the next president of the ANC. READ: President publicly endorses Dlamini-Zuma as successor She's viewed by many as a potential successor to President Jacob Zuma. Earlier this year Zuma praised her, saying she was capable and ready to lead the party. READ: Another boost for Ramaphosa's presidential bid But that was not the response when Dlamini-Zuma said on Twitter: Dlamini-Zuma has been endorsed for the top job by both the ANC Youth League and the ANC Women’s League. eNCA